--- tests/errors/unsupported_expressions.ml:45:3 --------------------------- side_effect (12/16) ---

  43 | 
  44 | let try_with value =
> 45 |   try value with
> 46 |   | Failure _ -> 0
  47 | 
  48 | let try_with_name value =
  49 |   try value with


Use a trivial matching for the `with` clause, like:

    try ... with exn -> ...

You can do a second matching on `exn` in the error handler if needed.

--- tests/errors/unsupported_expressions.ml:49:3 --------------------------- side_effect (13/16) ---

